---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import SectionSubnav from '../../components/SectionSubnav.astro';
import { aboutSubnav } from '../../data/nav';
import Cta from '../../components/Cta.astro';
---
<Base title="The Qi-House Ethos">
  <SectionSubnav items={aboutSubnav} active="/about/ethos" label="About section" />
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="About"
    title="The Qi-House Ethos"
    subtitle="Life is the practice of maintaining the power of choice."
  />

  <section class="bg-stone">
    <div class="container-content py-section-sm lg:py-section max-w-3xl space-y-12">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The Foundational Axiom</p>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate/90">
          No institution can govern choice. It can only influence it. The purpose of education is to
          strengthen an individual's ability to exercise choice responsibly.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal border-l-2 border-gold pl-6">
        <p class="font-display text-2xl text-navy italic mb-3">The objective is not a collection of techniques. The objective is the capacity to govern yourself under pressure.</p>
        <p class="text-slate/90">A student learns to perceive clearly, choose deliberately, and act with discipline — first in training, then in everyday life. That growth in confidence, focus, and accountability is the education we deliver.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-4">What This Means in Practice</p>
        <div class="text-slate/90 space-y-4">
          <p>Students develop self-governance through a consistent cycle of observation, action, and reflection. In training, they learn to pay attention to what is happening around them, understand their options, and make deliberate choices rather than reacting impulsively. Whether practicing a new skill, navigating a challenge, or working alongside others, they are encouraged to take responsibility for their decisions and follow through with discipline.</p>
          <p>Over time, these habits extend beyond the training floor. Students become more confident because they learn that progress comes from effort and consistency. They become more focused because they practice directing their attention toward what matters most. They become more resilient because they experience challenge, learn from mistakes, and discover that setbacks are opportunities for growth rather than reasons to quit.</p>
          <p>The ultimate goal is not simply to produce capable martial artists. It is to develop individuals who can think clearly, act responsibly, and contribute positively to their families, schools, workplaces, and communities. When students learn to govern themselves under pressure, they carry that capability into every area of life.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Cta />
</Base>
